<h4>Playing the Game</h4>
<div class="helpText">
<p>You can find a three button interface, right below the table of cards.
<button>New Game</button>
<button>Discard</button>
<button>Suggest Discard</button>
</p>
<p>
<button>New Game</button><br>
This will start a new game! If you haven't finished the hand on the screen it will disappear <strong>forever!</strong> You'll never know what might have happened!
</p>

<p>
<button>Discard</button><br>
You can pick which cards you'd like to discard! Just click on them and they'll develop a yellow glow. If you change your mind, click it again they'll go back to normal. Once you've decided which cards you'd like to get rid of, click the Discard button and they'll disappear <strong>forever!</strong> They'll be replaced with new cards. If you don't click any cards, the computer assumes you just want to keep all of them. Maybe you have a really great hand! At this point you'll get to see the computer's cards. You'll know who won! I hope you won! But if you didn't just click on New Game and try again!
</p>
<p>
<button>Suggest Discard</button><br>
Maybe you're not sure which cards you'd like to discard! Click on this button and the computer will suggest which cards you should get rid of. It'll turn them yellow. You don't have to accept the computer's suggestion! Click on a selected card to keep it, or click on an additional card to get rid of that one too. After you've made up your mind, click on Discard and they'll disappear <strong>forever!</strong>
</p>
</p>
</div>
